Course Overview

This course provides an introduction to important topics in statistical concepts and reasoning essential to quantitative medical research. This course is lectured by a total of three faculty:

  • Week 1 to 8: Dr. Boncho Ku
  • Week 9 to 16: Dr. Mimi Ko

Course Level

Introductory to intermediate

Prerequisites

None. However, we expect that students are familiar with basic statistics.

Weekly Topics

Course Schedule (Week 1 ~ Week 8)
Week Description Lecturer
Week 1 (2023.9.07) Introduction to statistics Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 2 (2023.09.14) Summary of data Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 3 (2023.09.21) Concept of probability Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 4 (2023.09.28) Random variables and probability distribution Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 5 (2023.10.05) Important probability distribution Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 6 (2023.10.12) Sampling distribution and statistical inference Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 7 (2023.10.19) Estimation and hypothesis testing Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 8 (2023.10.26) Correlation and Regression Dr. Boncho Ku
Week 9 (2023.11.02) Design of clinical studies Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 10 (2023.11.09) Analysis of continuous data (1) Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 11 (2023.11.16) Analysis of continuous data (2) Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 12 (2023.11.23) Analysis of categorical data (1) Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 13 (2023.11.30) Analysis of categorical data (2) Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 14 (2023.12.07) Meta Analysis Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 15 (2023.12.14) Sample size calculation Dr. Mimi Ko
Week 16 (2023.12.21) Final exam Dr. Mimi Ko

Materials

  1. Study Design and Statistical Analysis : A Practical Guide for Clinicians. Mitchell H. Katz. 2006. Cambridge University Press
  2. Medical Statistics: A Guide to SPSS, Data Analysis and Critical Appraisal. Berlinda Barton and Jennifer Peat. 2nd Edition. 2014. WILEY Blackwell
  3. Statistics: Concepts and Controversies. David S. Moore and Willian Notz. 10th Edition. 2020. W.H. Freeman
  4. Introduction to Statistical Methodology. Derek L. Sonderegger and Robert Buscaglia. https://bookdown.org/dereksonderegger/570/
  5. Introduction to Probability and Statistics Using R: G.Jay Kerns

Homework 1 (2023-02)

Due Date: 2023.10.04 23:00 (Wednesday)

  1. Describe a plausible explanation and examples for the robustness of median.

  2. Research the Q-Q plot (definition, usage, how to make it, and how to interprete).

  3. Simplify the formula of correlation coefficients

  4. Please summarize and express the characteristics of the data you are currently researching based on what you have learned in class, each in your own way.

This page is for Dr. Ku’s course material only.
